Explain limitation of secure perimeter

Secure perimeter - is a form of protection that consists of device or techniques added to the edge of a managed network

Seven Layers of the OSI Model
7. Application
Closest to the end user
Provides network services directly to applications
Examples: HTTP, FTP, SSH, DNS
6. Presentation
Translates data formats, encryption, compression
Ensures data is readable by the receiving system
Examples: SSL, MPEG, JPEG
5. Session
Manages sessions between applications
Handles setup, coordination, and termination of communication
Examples: APIs, Sockets, WinSock
4. Transport
Ensures reliable data transfer (error checking, flow control)
Provides end-to-end communication
Examples: TCP, UDP
3. Network
Determines the best path for data (routing)
Handles logical addressing (IP addresses)
Examples: IP, ICMP, IPSec
2. Data Link
Packages data into frames
Provides error detection and flow control at the link level
Examples: Ethernet, PPP, Switch, Bridge
1. Physical
Deals with hardware transmission of raw bits
Defines cables, connectors, and signaling
Examples: Coax, Fiber, Wireless, Hubs


